article.description: New Mexico St. 95, W. New Mexico 62
article.headline: New Mexico St. 95, W. New Mexico 62
article.linkText: New Mexico St. 95, W. New Mexico 62
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- Troy Gillenwater led New Mexico State with 21 points and six Aggies scored in double figures in a 95-62 victory over Western New Mexico University on Monday night. Gillenwater scored New Mexico State's first 10 points as the Aggies (2-0) pulled away with an early 10-0 run for a 17-4 lead and never looked back. New Mexico State shot 52.4 percent while the Mustangs (0-1) started the game 3 of 12 and finished 32.8 percent. The Aggies led by as many as 21 in the first half and were ahead 17 points at halftime. Western was led by Chad Carter's 14 points while TJ Riley had 11 and Jeron McIntosh had nine. NMSU opened the second half 7 of 11 from the field and pushed the lead to 26 in the first eight minutes. The Aggies outrebounded the undersized Mustangs 53-30 and scored 38 points in the paint.
